                            <comment id="321605" author="sergey" created="Mon, 27 Dec 2021 15:52:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 on master: &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/f45dcd0a-4980-4def-acdc-af770833ede4&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/f45dcd0a-4980-4def-acdc-af770833ede4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately, logs from my link don&apos;t include anything from qmt and it is not finally clear why it fails.&lt;br/&gt;
However, I believe the problem is caused by a too small limit. The test uses soft_least_qunit which is 1024 - it is equal to minimum possible qunit size. So if an MDT begins to create inodes and sends, for example, pre acquire request to a QMT until the end of creating 1024 inodes, QMT may set EDQUOT. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;mknod(/mnt/lustre/d2.sanity-quota/f2.sanity-quota-0567) error: Disk quota exceeded
total: 567 create in 0.67 seconds: 849.21 ops/second
Disk quotas for usr quota_usr (uid 60000):
     Filesystem  kbytes   quota   limit   grace   files   quota   limit   grace
    /mnt/lustre     846       0       0       -     564       0    1024       -
lustre-MDT0000_UUID
                    846       -       0       -     564       -    1024       -
lustre-MDT0001_UUID
                      0       -       0       -       0       -       0       -
lustre-MDT0002_UUID
                      0       -       0       -       0       -       0       -&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I added &quot;lfs quota -uv&quot; to sanity-quota_2 that passes and found that &quot;files&quot; and &quot;limit&quot; for MDT1 is 0 after the 1st run of createmany.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
